    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-05T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-05T15:00:00-05:00" n="174"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d174">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/9815</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-05T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 5, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1195. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 1165. <persName>Frothingham</persName>. Embassy’s 1178, August 19, 1 p.m.,
                    your 1259.<note n="1" xml:id="d174fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1036">p. 1036</ref>.</note>
                    Conference here has determined advisable that conference plan extend to all
                    cases other than those excepted in original proposition by War Trade Board
                    embodied in despatch July 1.<note n="2" xml:id="d174fn2">Despatch not
                        printed.</note> This result has been communicated to French authorities
                    through <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> and
                    recommended to French authorities through French representative, Washington.
                    Italians make proposal to agree conference plan to extent of persons on refusal
                    lists but not other enemy persons. Washington conference including Italian
                    representative agree desirable conference plan be adopted in full by all
                    governments represented by conferees. This result communicated Italian
                    authorities through <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWAW1"
                        >Stewart</persName> at Rome and recommended to Italian authorities by
                    Italian representative in Washington. Act pending final agreement according
                    instructions our 1133, Aug. 27 [<hi rend="italic">31</hi>], and despatch August
                        30.<note n="2" xml:id="d174fn3">Despatch not printed.</note> Hereafter in
                    cabling reference enemy trade license conference do not mark cable for <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_FPj1">Fuller</persName> but simply send as War
                    Trade Board cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
